  "an9.14:1.1": "Numbered Discourses 9 ",
  "an9.14:2.1": "2 The Lion’s Roar ",
  "an9.14:3.1": "14 With Samiddhi",
  "an9.14:4.1": "Then Venerable Samiddhi went up to Venerable Sāriputta,",
  "an9.14:4.2": "bowed, and stood to one side.",
  "an9.14:4.3": "Venerable Sāriputta said to him:",
  "an9.14:5.1": "“Samiddhi, based on what do thoughts arise in a person?”",
  "an9.14:5.2": "“Based on name and form, sir.”",
  "an9.14:6.1": "“Where do they become diversified?”",
  "an9.14:6.2": "“In the elements.”",
  "an9.14:7.1": "“What is their origin?”",
  "an9.14:7.2": "“Contact is their origin.”",
  "an9.14:8.1": "“What is their meeting place?”",
  "an9.14:8.2": "“Feeling is their meeting place.”",
  "an9.14:9.1": "“What is their chief?”",
  "an9.14:9.2": "“Samadhi is their chief.”",
  "an9.14:10.1": "“What is their ruler?”",
  "an9.14:10.2": "“Mindfulness is their ruler.”",
  "an9.14:11.1": "“What is their overseer?”",
  "an9.14:11.2": "“Wisdom is their overseer.”",
  "an9.14:12.1": "“What is their core?”",
  "an9.14:12.2": "“Freedom is their core.”",
  "an9.14:13.1": "“What is their culmination?”",
  "an9.14:13.2": "“They culminate in the deathless.”",
  "an9.14:14.1": "“Samiddhi, when you were asked what is the basis on which thoughts arise in a person, you answered ‘name and form’.",
  "an9.14:14.2": "When you were asked …",
  "an9.14:14.9": "what is their culmination, you answered ‘the deathless’.",
  "an9.14:14.10": "Good, good, Samiddhi!",
  "an9.14:14.11": "It’s good that you answered each question. But don’t get conceited because of that.”"
}